que illi pedes, ac manus conſtrinxiſie propte • quam exquiſita dry land encompaſſing it, and it would doe both, if God did not bound it, if he had not ſaid, Hitherto ſhalt thou come, but no further, and here ſhall thy proud waves be ſtaied; did not God put an everlaſting law upon it, it would be lawleſſe, Gen. 1. 10. the text ſaith, That the gathering together of waters, God called ſeas;
God gathered them together, thruſt them together into one place, and there ſet a watch upon them, put them in priſon, bound them Deiprovidentiam dioitur. Pſal. 95. 4. in chaines, for he ſaw what an unruly element it was, and how ſoone it would diſturbe all, if left to it's own guidance. So Job 38. 10. He hath ſet bounds to it, barrs and doors to keepe it in. He locks and bolts it in by his mighty power. And then Jobs meaning may be this. Am I an over-whelming tyrant or oppreſſour, a ſwallower up of the poore, &c. that thou doſt thus impriſon and reſtrain me?

The word ſignifies to mourne and repent, as well as to comfort;
