Secondly, note, if the preſence of God chaſtning, be ſo grievous, what will his preſence be puniſhing and tormenting: If afflictions, which are but for tryall, and are all ſteep'd in love, be ſo grievous; what, will thoſe terrours be, which all ſteept in
pure, everlaſting wrath? If his chaſtnings be ſo intolerable to ſome of his deareſt friends, what will his revenges be to all his profeſſed enemies? Wi •••• men are now burden'd with the preſence of God, becau ••
